4.3. Offloading decision optimization

Let ğ´ = [ğ‘1, ğ‘2, â€¦ , ğ‘ğ‘ ] be the offloading decisions for all users. In the initial state, it is assumed that the offloading decision is an all-
one matrix, that is, all users choose to offload the computing of tasks, which is denoted as ğ´0. Coordinate descent requires multiple iterations to find the optimal value. At the ğ‘™ âˆ’ 1 (ğ‘™ = 1, 2, â€¦) iteration, let ğ´ğ‘™âˆ’1 represent the offloading decision at this time. Then ğ‘‰ (ğ´ğ‘™âˆ’1) represents the optimal value of the formula when offloading decision is ğ´ğ‘™âˆ’1. The
coordinate descent method changes the offloading decision of only one user at a time during one iteration. Let ğ‘„ğ‘™ğ‘› denote the gain of the system at the ğ‘™th iteration, which can be expressed as:

ğ‘„ğ‘™ğ‘› = ğ‘‰ (ğ´ğ‘™âˆ’1) âˆ’ ğ‘‰ (ğ´ğ‘™âˆ’1 (ğ‘›))

